00:03:22.810 --> 00:03:26.650
PROFESSOR: So we get rid of
all of the quantum character

00:03:26.650 --> 00:03:29.870
of the electromagnetic
field in two stages.

00:03:32.950 --> 00:03:36.900
One is the following,
well, we want

00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:40.760
to describe the interactions
of atoms with laser fields.

00:03:40.760 --> 00:03:43.080
And that means the
electromagnetic field

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:45.110
is in a coherent state.

00:03:45.110 --> 00:03:46.850
And you know from
several weeks ago,

00:03:46.850 --> 00:03:48.840
the coherent state
is a superposition

00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:51.050
of a [INAUDIBLE] states,
coherent superposition

00:03:51.050 --> 00:03:53.520
and such, so they're
really photons inside.

00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:58.710
It's a fully quantized
description of the laser beam.

00:03:58.710 --> 00:04:01.450
But now-- and this is something
if you're not familiar,

00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:03.170
you should really
look up-- there

00:04:03.170 --> 00:04:09.360
is an exact canonical
transformation

00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:13.060
where you transform
your Hamiltonian--

00:04:13.060 --> 00:04:15.670
you do, so to speak, a
basis transformation--

00:04:15.670 --> 00:04:17.430
to another Hamiltonian.

00:04:17.430 --> 00:04:23.100
And the result is, after
this unitary transformation,

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:26.510
the coherent state is
transformed to the vacuum

00:04:26.510 --> 00:04:28.000
state.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:31.510
So in other words, the
quantized electromagnetic field

00:04:31.510 --> 00:04:33.140
is no longer in
the coherent state,

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:36.330
it's in the vacuum state.

00:04:36.330 --> 00:04:41.000
But what appears
instead is a purely

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:43.670
classical electromagnetic field.

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:46.270
A c number.

00:04:46.270 --> 00:04:49.250
So you can sort of say--
I'm waving my hands now--

00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:50.970
the coherent state
is the vacuum,

00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:53.760
with a displacement operator.

00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:56.420
All the quantumness of
the electromagnetic field

00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:58.130
is in the vacuum
state, and that's

00:04:58.130 --> 00:04:59.940
something we have
to keep because this

00:04:59.940 --> 00:05:02.300
is responsible for
spontaneous emission quantum

00:05:02.300 --> 00:05:04.100
fluctuations and such.

00:05:04.100 --> 00:05:06.080
But the displacement
operator, which

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:09.130
gives us an arbitrary
coherent state, that

00:05:09.130 --> 00:05:11.807
can be absorbed by
completely treating

00:05:11.807 --> 00:05:13.390
the electromagnetic
field classically.

00:05:18.290 --> 00:05:22.520
So therefore, we take the fully
quantized electromagnetic field

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:28.000
and we replace it now by a
classical field, and simply

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.120
the vacuum fluctuation.

00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:32.690
So there are no
photons around anymore.

00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:36.770
There is the vacuum ready
to absorb the photons,

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:39.470
and then there's a classical
electromagnetic field,

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:40.980
which drives the atoms.

00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:44.980
And, of course, the classical
electromagnetic field

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:47.740
is not changing because
of absorption emission,

00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:51.860
because it's a c number
in our Hamiltonian.

00:05:51.860 --> 00:05:54.400
So this is an important
conceptual step,

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:56.030
and it's the first
step in how we

00:05:56.030 --> 00:05:58.965
get rid of the quantum nature
of the electromagnetic field

00:05:58.965 --> 00:06:01.060
when it interacts with
atoms mechanically.

00:06:05.061 --> 00:06:05.560
OK.

