00:13:08.360 --> 00:13:12.200
And this was the in
quadrature component, v.

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:16.500
So it is only the part, v, of
the Optical Bloch vector which

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:18.990
is responsible for
exchanging energy

00:13:18.990 --> 00:13:21.694
with the electromagnetic field.

00:13:21.694 --> 00:13:31.070
And we can also, by dividing
by the energy of a photon,

00:13:31.070 --> 00:13:33.490
