number of absorbed photons.

00:13:33.490 --> 00:13:35.810
But we did that already when
we discussed Optical Bloch

00:13:35.810 --> 00:13:36.309
Equations.

00:13:38.910 --> 00:13:43.160
OK, so that was our look back
on the Optical Bloch Equation,

00:13:43.160 --> 00:13:45.940
the solution for the
oscillating dipole moment,

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:50.080
and now we are ready to
put everything together.

00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:52.800
So we want to know the force.

00:13:52.800 --> 00:13:57.140
The force, using Heisenberg's
Equation of Motion

00:13:57.140 --> 00:14:01.340
for the momentum derivative
is the expectation value

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:08.180
of the operator, which is the
gradient of the Hamiltonian.

00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:08.820
OK.

00:14:08.820 --> 00:14:11.460
So now we have to take the
gradient of the Hamiltonian.

00:14:14.450 --> 00:14:16.250
This is the only
expression, actually,

00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:19.405
today, I would've liked to just
write it down, and build it

00:14:19.405 --> 00:14:20.470
up piece by piece.

00:14:20.470 --> 00:14:22.520
But let me step you through.

00:14:22.520 --> 00:14:24.085
We want to take the gradient.

00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:32.920
The dipole operator of the atom
does not have an r dependence,

00:14:32.920 --> 00:14:35.830
it's just x on the
atom, wherever it is.

00:14:35.830 --> 00:14:40.130
But the gradient with respect
to the center of mass position

00:14:40.130 --> 00:14:42.870
from the atoms comes
from the operator

00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:45.450
of the electromagnetic field.

00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:47.520
So in other words,
what this involves

00:14:47.520 --> 00:14:52.430
is the gradient of the
operator of the fully quantized

00:14:52.430 --> 00:14:54.300
electromagnetic field.

00:14:54.300 --> 00:14:58.770
But we have already written
at the electromagnetic field

00:14:58.770 --> 00:15:05.080
as an external
electromagnetic field--

00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:07.640
classical electromagnetic
field-- plus a vacuum

00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:09.050
fluctuations.

00:15:09.050 --> 00:15:12.980
But the vacuum
fluctuations are symmetric.

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.980
There is nothing which
tells vacuum fluctuations

00:15:14.980 --> 00:15:16.600
what is left and what is right.

00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:18.580
So therefore, the
derivative only

00:15:18.580 --> 00:15:22.840
acts on the classical
