01:28:12.640 --> 01:28:16.320
kv-- how well I can
resolve it, depends

01:28:16.320 --> 01:28:18.520
on the width of the
atomic transition.

01:28:18.520 --> 01:28:20.840
The narrower the
atomic transition,

01:28:20.840 --> 01:28:25.910
the more the Doppler effect
can steer the laser cooling--

01:28:25.910 --> 01:28:28.190
the Raman process--
towards lower velocity,

01:28:28.190 --> 01:28:30.470
not towards higher velocity.

01:28:30.470 --> 01:28:33.510
So that's the natural result
that the-- or an expected

01:28:33.510 --> 01:28:37.711
